content.description: Start matched with good hold.  Throw left into deep slot.  Top-out
content.location: Right of corner on face of the cube.
Right corner of cube.  Across trail from Arete Boulder.

content.description: Sit with feet at a low rail, right hand in lower slot, and left hand on an intermediate. Bump through a sharp hold and up into the upper pocket. Match, get high feet, and move out right to a rounded crimp. Make a cruxy stab to good holds above and cruise to the top.
content.location: Middle of the main face on the cube boulder

content.description: Using deep pocket for hand and low pocket for foot, climb straight up boulder.  A bit more tricky.
content.location: Right of Layed back and Slot

content.description: Start low on the left face of the Cube boulder.  Straight up, one big move, top out.
content.location: Left side of the Cube boulder, next to tree.

content.description: Starting on same jug as Slot, climb straight up using fins.

My apologies for mudding up the system more with additional traverse problems on this boulder, but this line is definitive and good quality starting on the S face of the boulder and finishing on the NE arete.  

  SDS on large jug flake left of the corner and move up and right though crimps.  Hit the arete pinch and round the corner staying low and matching the large angling flake.  Make the long reach to the vertical slot/pocket and continue moving low and right matching in the slot/pocket.  Make a final crux sequence using side-pull edges and a pinch to get you to the NE arete with jugs and flake that leads to a juggy top-out.
content.location: Cube Boulder - S face to NE arete

content.description: Left side of boulder from the corner problem, start low on large flake and work your way around the boulder moving left to right.  Most people top out above the slot climb, but for a greater challenge keep going all the way and end on the easier far corner.
content.location: Start low and left of the corner problem, and move left to right around the Cube.

content.description: Start as far toward the man-eater boulder as possible on the face opposite the trail,(south side). Traverse to the right staying low and not using the top edge. Climb around the corner and top out using either the slot or keep going to top out using off the pocket.
content.protection: A couple of pads on the rock and stump by the corner

content.description: Start low and climb corner, top-out right on jugs.
The Cube is a large boulder that sits immediatly below the trail, below the overlook. Many good classics exist here and good warm-ups too.
